00:02:37.610 --> 00:02:40.440
In 40 years in the
corporate world,

00:02:40.440 --> 00:02:47.520
I came to realize that the
corporate world has the three

00:02:47.520 --> 00:02:51.450
conditions for abuse
to be systemic.

00:02:54.350 --> 00:03:00.080
And it's interesting, isn't
it, that abuse is a very, very

00:03:00.080 --> 00:03:02.315
topical dynamic at the moment.

00:03:02.315 --> 00:03:05.130
And quite rightly so.

00:03:05.130 --> 00:03:09.930
Those three conditions
are we give power

00:03:09.930 --> 00:03:13.200
to people over other people.

00:03:13.200 --> 00:03:16.610
We certainly do that
in the corporate world.

00:03:16.610 --> 00:03:23.130
And I don't really mind
how benign your manager is

00:03:23.130 --> 00:03:26.190
or how loving or caring
they are, particularly

00:03:26.190 --> 00:03:31.410
as we come up to par for
evaluation, what they think

00:03:31.410 --> 00:03:37.050
and the power that they have
over us is definitely a factor.

00:03:40.140 --> 00:03:45.540
The second condition is fear.

00:03:45.540 --> 00:03:48.760
Corporations are
organized in hierarchies,

00:03:48.760 --> 00:03:54.450
and there are a number of levels
even in this wonderful company.

00:03:54.450 --> 00:03:59.070
And it was the hierarchy and
the fear of the hierarchy that

00:03:59.070 --> 00:04:01.980
